	\section*{\centering \bf \large ABSTRACT}
			
	\vspace*{20pt}
		\par
	
 
 
In today’s fast-paced urban environments, locating clean and accessible public restrooms remains a common challenge. LooLocator is an innovative smart system designed to address this issue by helping users quickly find nearby public restrooms using GPS-based location tracking. The system integrates IoT technology, QR code authentication, and a secure digital payment module to deliver a seamless and hygienic restroom experience.\vspace{12pt}\newline
The application allows users to locate available restrooms on an interactive map, view details such as accessibility, hygiene rating, and availability status, and unlock restroom doors through a simple digital interface. Each restroom pod is equipped with an IoT-enabled locking system that can be remotely controlled once payment is verified, ensuring both convenience and security. Administrators have access to a web-based dashboard to monitor restroom usage, manage maintenance requests, track revenue analytics, and remotely unlock doors in emergency situations.\vspace{12pt}\newline
By combining smart technologies like IoT, GPS, and data analytics, LooLocator enhances urban sanitation infrastructure and improves user convenience. It also enables authorities to maintain hygiene standards, optimize resource management, and ensure transparency in public facility operations. Thus, LooLocator contributes to the development of smart cities by transforming traditional public restrooms into intelligent, user-friendly, and data-driven spaces.




