	\section{General Background}
	
	

India is experiencing rapid urbanization, with increasing migration from rural areas to cities, a surge in tourism, and growing daily commutes placing significant stress on urban infrastructure. Among essential urban amenities, public restrooms are often neglected, resulting in poor maintenance, lack of hygiene, and insufficient mapping or monitoring. The absence of clean and accessible facilities impacts not only general comfort but also public health, as unhygienic toilets can contribute to the spread of diseases and environmental pollution. Restricted restroom access disproportionately affects vulnerable groups, including women, children, senior citizens, and people with disabilities, limiting their mobility and participation in public life. Although modern technology has improved services such as transportation, digital navigation, and communication, restroom accessibility remains largely unaddressed.\vspace{12pt}\newline

This pressing need for accessible, hygienic, and well-managed public restrooms has created an opportunity for smart, data-driven solutions. **LooLocator** aims to bridge this gap by providing a technology-enabled platform that helps users locate nearby public restrooms, view real-time availability, and access clean facilities efficiently. By integrating GPS, IoT-enabled door control, QR code verification, and usage analytics, LooLocator not only improves user convenience but also assists authorities and service providers in monitoring, maintaining, and optimizing public restroom infrastructure. This innovative approach ensures hygiene, safety, and accessibility for all, making urban spaces more inclusive and user-friendly.\vspace{12pt}


  

	
	\section{Objective}
	The core objective of this project is to develop LooLocator, a smart public restroom finder application that delivers timely, accurate, and location-specific information to users. The system aims to help users locate nearby public restrooms using GPS and provide comprehensive details for each facility, including the type (male, female, or unisex), accessibility for differently-abled individuals, cleanliness ratings based on user feedback, payment status, and operating hours. Additionally, LooLocator enables users to submit reviews, rate cleanliness, and report issues such as closures or maintenance problems. Beyond user convenience, the project supports broader goals of the Swachh Bharat Mission and smart city initiatives by bridging the information gap between users, urban planners, and service providers, thereby contributing to improved hygiene, accessibility, and effective management of public restroom infrastructure.\vspace{12pt}
	
    \section{Scope}
The scope of LooLocator encompasses designing and implementing a comprehensive smart public restroom finder system that serves both users and administrators. For users, the application provides real-time location-based restroom information, including accessibility, cleanliness, operating hours, and payment requirements. It enables users to rate facilities, submit feedback, and report issues, creating a community-driven quality monitoring mechanism. For administrators and service providers, the system offers tools to manage restroom data, monitor usage patterns, track maintenance needs, and analyze feedback for operational improvements. The project also integrates IoT-enabled features, such as smart locks, to automate restroom access based on verified usage or payments. While the system is focused on urban environments with GPS-enabled devices, it can be extended to include web and mobile platforms, supporting smart city initiatives, enhancing public hygiene, and bridging the information gap between citizens and municipal authorities.\\
