\section{Proposed system}
The proposed LooLocator system is a technologically advanced and socially impactful solution designed to modernize the way public restrooms are located, accessed, and managed. With increasing urbanization and the growing need for hygienic public infrastructure, the system leverages modern technologies such as GPS, QR code authentication, IoT-based smart locking systems, mobile applications, and cloud computing to deliver a real-time, interactive restroom management solution. It is specifically tailored to overcome the limitations of traditional restroom finding methods and existing apps, which often suffer from outdated information, lack of automation, and poor user experience.\vspace{12pt}\newline

At its core, LooLocator operates through a mobile application available on Android and iOS platforms. This application helps users identify nearby public restrooms using real-time GPS tracking and provides detailed information including distance, gender-specific access (male/female), cleanliness ratings, availability, and accessibility features such as wheelchair ramps. The interface is designed to be intuitive, multilingual, and inclusive, ensuring that users from diverse backgrounds can easily navigate and use the platform.\vspace{12pt}\newline

The system’s smart access mechanism is one of its defining features. Restroom doors are equipped with IoT-enabled smart locks connected to microcontrollers such as Arduino or Raspberry Pi. When a user arrives at a selected restroom, they can scan a QR code displayed at the entrance. The system verifies the scan, processes digital payments if required (via UPI, Google Pay, Paytm, etc.), and triggers the IoT module to remotely unlock the door. This secure, contactless process not only enhances hygiene and safety but also ensures controlled access and data logging for usage analytics.\vspace{12pt}\newline

In addition to user-side features, the admin panel provides robust tools for restroom owners or municipal administrators. Through a cloud-based dashboard, administrators can add or update restroom listings, monitor usage logs in real-time, remotely control access during emergencies, and receive reports of maintenance or cleanliness issues submitted by users. The admin panel is also equipped with analytics capabilities to visualize trends, usage peaks, hygiene feedback, and system health, enabling proactive maintenance and decision-making.\vspace{12pt}\newline

The system is designed for scalability and modularity, making it adaptable to urban, semi-urban, or rural contexts. It supports third-party integrations such as Google Maps APIs for location services, Firebase or MySQL for database management, and payment gateways like Razorpay or PhonePe. The IoT infrastructure uses Wi-Fi or GSM modules to maintain seamless communication with the cloud server.\vspace{12pt}\newline

Ultimately, LooLocator is not just a location service—it is a smart public sanitation ecosystem. It fills the existing technological and infrastructural gaps in sanitation services, aligns with national initiatives like Swachh Bharat Abhiyan and Smart Cities Mission, and promotes digital hygiene awareness, safety, and convenience for millions of urban dwellers.\vspace{12pt}\newline


