\section{Module Description}
The proposed system comprises multiple interdependent modules designed to streamline public restroom discovery, access, and management. These modules collaboratively enhance user convenience and provide administrators with the tools to monitor and control facilities efficiently.

\subsection{ User Location and Map Module (Location Display Module)}
This module leverages GPS technology to determine the user’s real-time location and displays nearby public restrooms on an interactive map. By integrating services like Google Maps API, the module ensures high accuracy and provides a visual representation of available restrooms, enabling users to make quick, location-based decisions.

\subsection{ Restroom Information Display Module}
This module showcases detailed information about each restroom, including gender type (male/female), accessibility options (such as wheelchair access), and payment status (free or paid). It provides users with essential data needed to choose restrooms based on comfort, safety, and personal requirements.

\subsection{ Filter and Search Module}
This component allows users to refine their restroom search by applying various filters. Users can filter restrooms by type, accessibility features, and payment status. This targeted search functionality ensures that users find the most suitable restroom option in minimal time, based on individual preferences and requirements.

\subsection{ QR Code Scan and Payment Module}
This module allows users to scan a QR code at the restroom entrance, which opens a secure interface to initiate or complete a digital payment. The integration of mobile wallets (e.g., UPI, Paytm, Google Pay) makes the transaction process seamless. This also serves as a verification step before unlocking the door, improving both access control and hygiene.

\subsection{ IoT-Based Smart Door Unlock Module}
This module forms the core of the smart restroom system, where IoT devices control physical access to the restroom. After successful QR scan and payment, the IoT-enabled system receives a trigger to unlock the restroom door remotely. The module also logs access times, user IDs, and unlock events, allowing for real-time monitoring and enhanced security.

\subsection{ Admin Management Module}
This module is built for system administrators and offers functionalities such as adding and managing restroom listings, monitoring unlock logs, responding to reported issues, and remotely controlling restroom doors in case of emergencies or technical failures. The admin dashboard includes analytical tools and alert notifications, helping administrators maintain hygiene standards, improve service delivery, and ensure system integrity.

