\section{Backend Testing} 
API testing for the Tamil to Malayalam Dictionary App was conducted using Postman to ensure the backend services function correctly, handle requests efficiently, and return expected responses. The testing process included verifying user authentication by checking login and registration endpoints, ensuring secure access control, and validating hashed passwords. The word search and translation functionalities were tested by sending GET requests to retrieve word details, meanings, translations, synonyms, and antonyms while handling errors for invalid inputs. Admin functionalities such as adding, updating, and deleting words were tested using POST, PUT, and DELETE requests to confirm proper data management and validation rules. Performance and load testing were performed to measure response times under different loads and ensure system stability under high traffic. Additionally, error handling tests covered scenarios like missing parameters, invalid data formats, and unauthorized access, ensuring meaningful error messages and secure API behavior. The successful completion of these tests validated the application's reliability, accuracy, and performance, ensuring a seamless and user-friendly experience.

